That's sort of the reason to get specific there, though: technically rust is only for iron, but its also occasionally used as a general term for oxidation of metals. Something that was made of copper or chrome wouldn't oxidize in the way that they normally do, however, and form a protective shell of patina- they would corrode in the same way that iron compounds do. One of those  things.





